      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. They made it to the final round for a senior dev role here in Austin, so it's a tough one. They were really strong in system design and had great culture fit, but we just went with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. Can you draft something professional and kind so we don't burn a bridge?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a draft rejection email that's both professional and kind:\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We were truly impressed by your exceptional system design skills and your alignment with our company culture, and we appreciate the time and effort you took to interview with us.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience with our specific cloud stack aligns more closely with our current needs. Please know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely impressed by your qualifications and fit for our team.\n\nWe recognize that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that it's not a reflection on your abilities or potential as a developer. We're confident that you will find a great opportunity that aligns with your skills and interests, and we wish you all the best in your job search.\n\nIf you have any questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to reach out to me directly. We appreciate your interest in joining our team and hope to have the chance to work with you in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nI hope this draft helps! Remember, it's a bit like a",
